cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC

Reasoning: 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper uses computational methods to analyze a large dataset of workplace sexual harassment experiences. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The study focuses on experiences shared on a website, which can be seen as a social network. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper addresses a societal issue, namely workplace sexism and sexual harassment. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The computational framework used in this study can be seen as a software engineering approach. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The study aims to understand how people experience workplace sexism and sexual harassment, which can be seen as a human-computer interaction issue.
